The paper focuses on the design and optimization of gaits for robot locomotion, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach uses data-driven methods to learn locomotion primitives, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach also involves contextual policy search, which is a control theory technique (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the approach using simulations, which may involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
